  "body": "This was reported via Gitter. If you run `truffle test` multiple times after running `truffle init`, without running any other command between, you'll see that Truffle recompiles each time. We should instead make the compile process update the `.sol.js` files in place before copying over to a temp directory so compiling isn't required a second time. \n\nNote that you can remove this issue by running `truffle init`, `truffle compile` then `truffle test`. This will create a `.sol.js` file which `truffle test` will then copy over, satisfying the check that determines if recompilation is needed.\n\n```\n$ truffle version\nTruffle v2.0.4\n$ truffle init\n$ truffle test\nCompiling ConvertLib.sol...\nCompiling MetaCoin.sol...\nCompiling Migrations.sol...\n\n\n  Contract: MetaCoin\n    ✓ should put 10000 MetaCoin in the first account\n    ✓ should call a function that depends on a linked library   (60ms)\n    ✓ should send coin correctly (114ms)\n\n\n  3 passing (2s)\n\n$ truffle test\nCompiling ConvertLib.sol...\nCompiling MetaCoin.sol...\nCompiling Migrations.sol...\n\n\n  Contract: MetaCoin\n    ✓ should put 10000 MetaCoin in the first account\n    ✓ should call a function that depends on a linked library   (55ms)\n    ✓ should send coin correctly (117ms)\n\n\n  3 passing (2s)\n\n```\n",
